13 years ago (wow) I decided I would fly to Dallas and try out to be one of America’s Sweethearts. THE Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders…And I had absolutely no idea what I was in for! It was one for the most amazing, character building, life shaping experiences I would have all crammed into the span of one year! My time in Dallas was short, but I am so blessed to know I have friendships/ a sisterhood that will last a lifetime. 🩷 To be able to watch the progression of excellence in this organization in person is something incredibly noteworthy! What an amazing weekend. I’m exhausted…. But how bout we do it again next year?… oh and what a win also?! #gocowboys  #dccsisterhood #dallascowboyscheerleaders

It’s New Year’s Eve!! What an amazing year it has been. Lots of ups and downs, laughter and tears, resting and forging onward. So fun to look back on all of these wonderful, love filled, memorable moments. Excited for new beginnings and a fresh new year for all. 🤍

At the end of last year a woman approached me in a dressing room, after I had been teaching a dance workshop and asked if she could pray with me. We had a brief conversation previously about serving in church, but I wasn’t expecting the adamant request to pray with me specifically since we were in a group.  It was a really special moment and I could feel Gods hand all over it. She shared, what I believe, was a prophetic word with me that was such a blessing. To roughly explain, in part, she mentioned 2nd Corinthians 10:5 -taking thoughts captive and making them obedient to Christ, as well as “protecting my land.” - which meant a few different things to me. 

This is a video of us walking our land this morning. As we walked I spent time praying over every little part of it. We also talked about our visions of it for the future. We’ve had big plans for this place and it’s been a looooong journey toward keeping a heart position where peace and freedom can consistently reign free here (for me- Leith would live here in a tree stand if he could)… But this year feels different, I’m trusting Gods timing and surrendering to his will. His plans are ALWAYS greater than mine. 🤍🤍🤍🤍
